title: [Datasets page] Improve code snippet for empty worskpace
body:
The current code snippet has caused several confusions for first-time users. The main issue is that is focused on more complex installations (several workspaces, custom API keys) and that is misaligned with our docs (where we don't use the `rb.init()` method). When we start having more complex installations the docs will recommend to set ENVs for the api key and url anyway.

I'd recommend to have this code snippet instead:

```python
import rubrix as rb

# If you are using the default installation you can skip this line
rb.set_workspace("${ws}")

rb.log(
  rb.TextClassificationRecord(inputs="my first rubrix example"), 
  name='example-dataset'
)
```

Another option is to keep the rb.init but commented out with a message like this:

`# If you have configured your own API url and key, run this line`

title: [Rule] Modify the client API to the server's weak supervision feature
body:
This PR contains basically 3 changes:
- rename `rules_from_dataset` to `load_rules`. I think this is more consistent with the `rb.load` terminology to "load" a list of records from the server.
- move `rule_metrics` to `Rule.metrics()`. I think it just makes sense to add this as a method to the `Rule` class. Now it also returns just a `dict`, instead of a pydantic model, which I feel is not necessary yet. The main use case is just to view those metrics in your notebook, so a dict I think is enough.
- The `RubrixClient` is now using directly the SDK models. I think the intermediate models that were defined in `_models` are not really necessary, since we already have a user-facing `Rule` class.

title: [LabelModel] Improve Snorkel to not modify the passed in WeakLabels object
body:
Right now, the label model `Snorkel` (in contrast to the `FlyingSquid` label model) will modify the passed in `WeakLabels` object, if the label2int mapping is not compatible with the snorkel model (that is -1 for "abstention", and sequential integers for the labels). This is not done in a transparent way and can lead to confusion if you want to further use the `WeakLabels` object afterward.

This PRs modifies `Snorkel` so that it creates a remapped copy of the weak label matrix or annotation array, when using the `fit`, `predict` or `score` method. So the `WeakLabels` object is not modified.
